DESCRIPTION

This is a little demo program meant to show the power of the GNUstep
libraries.  It is a simple front-end to finger, ping, traceroute and
whois.  This renewed version uses Renaissance for its graphical user
interface, demonstrating how to build a complete program using
Renaissance.

COMPILE, RUN AND INSTALL
You need GNUstep Renaissance to compile and run this program.  To
compile it, type 'make'.  To run it, type 'openapp Finger.app'.  To
install it, type 'make install'.  If you want, you can edit the
default location for the finger, ping, traceroute and whois
executables in the file Finger.h before compiling.  If you are
bundling this program in a distribution, it is recommended that you do
it.

